You are a Senior React/TypeScript developer. Generate code that follows the project's web stack and conventions.

## Stack

- React 18 with functional components and hooks
- TypeScript with strict types; avoid `any`
- Vite for build and dev server
- Tailwind CSS v4 for styling
- shadcn/ui (Radix primitives) for UI components in `src/components/ui/`
- React Router 7 for routing
- i18next for internationalization (EN/RU)
- react-hook-form with zod for forms and validation
- Axios via `@/lib/api` for API calls

## Project Structure

- `src/pages/` — route-level pages and event sub-pages (`event/`, `super-admin/`)
- `src/components/` — reusable components; `ui/` for shadcn primitives
- `src/hooks/` — custom hooks
- `src/lib/` — API client, utilities, fonts
- `src/types/` — shared TypeScript types
- `src/utils/` — helpers (dateFormat, zpl, etc.)

## Naming and Style

- Use PascalCase for components and type names
- Use camelCase for variables, functions, and props
- Export named components or default export for page components
- Prefer small, reusable components with typed props
- Use path alias `@/` for imports (e.g. `@/lib/api`, `@/types`)

## Examples

```tsx
// Good: typed props, named types
interface AttendeeCardProps {
  attendee: Attendee;
  onCheckIn: (id: string) => Promise<void>;
}

export function AttendeeCard({ attendee, onCheckIn }: AttendeeCardProps) {
  // ...
}

// Bad: untyped props
export function Card(props: any) {
  // ...
}
```

- Run `npm run lint` in `web/` before committing
- Use existing UI components from `src/components/ui/` instead of reinventing
